99-109: _⚠️ Potential issue_

**Add null check and handle edge cases in IsOverridable method.**

The IsOverridable method lacks a null check for the `symbol` parameter, which could cause a NullReferenceException.


Apply this diff to add the null check and improve edge case handling:

```diff
[MethodImpl(MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining)]
public static bool IsOverridable(this ISymbol symbol)
{
+    if (symbol is null)
+    {
+        return false;
+    }
+
    return symbol switch
    {
        IMethodSymbol { IsStatic: true } or IPropertySymbol { IsStatic: true } => false,
        _ when symbol.ContainingType?.TypeKind == TypeKind.Interface => true,
        _ => !symbol.IsSealed &&
              (symbol.IsVirtual || symbol.IsAbstract || symbol is { IsOverride: true, IsSealed: false }),
    };
}
```


